        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 11:54AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1153 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Bowdon to Tennant to New Site, and moving east at
50 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Franklin, Plant Yates, Roopville, Tyus, Powers Crossroads,
Roosterville, Handy, Waresville, Frolona, Lowell, Texas, Plant
Wansley, Glenn, Blackjack Mountain, Corinth, Ephesus, Whitesburg,
Centralhatchee, and Harrisonville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM EDT for northwestern
and west central Georgia.</instruction>
